      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">A Brief History</h2>
      <p>Scrabble was invented during the Great Depression by Alfred Mosher Butts, an unemployed architect from New York. He studied letter frequency in newspapers to determine tile distribution and point values — a system so well-designed that it has barely changed since the 1930s.</p>

